        <updateDate>2012-04-02T18:45:09Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Presidential Allowance Modernization Act - Revises provisions relating to presidential pensions to&nbsp;allow former&nbsp;Presidents&nbsp;an annuity&nbsp;of $200,000&nbsp;and an additional monetary&nbsp;allowance&nbsp;of $200,000 per year. Reduces such pension by the amount that a President's adjusted gross income in a taxable year exceeds $400,000.&nbsp; </p> <p>Increases from $20,000 to $100,000 the annual annuity of a surviving spouse of a former President. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
